The course consists of preparatory video lectues, students' independent work and four workshops where progress of students' work is discussed and results will be presented. The preparatory part outlines the problematic to consider when tackling relations between literarature and myth in general education, and offers examples of possible methodical solutions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is specifically designed as a preparation for teaching the course about the relations between literature and folklore in high school, its broader objective is preparation for teaching analoguous subject matter at other levels of general education or in other subjects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Design and presentation of a learning element. Feedback to other students' work.
